## Test coverage map (`packages/motion-gpu/src/tests`)

| Area | Coverage focus |
| --- | --- |
| Public API | Root and advanced export contracts. |
| `FragCanvas` | WebGPU unavailable behavior, error callback + overlay toggling. |
| Context hooks | Runtime context access constraints and exposed controls. |
| Scheduler | ordering, invalidation modes, stage callbacks, diagnostics/profiling. |
| Material | contract validation, includes/defines, signature behavior, caching. |
| Uniforms | type inference, layout alignment, packing behavior. |
| Textures | defaults, size/update/mipmap helpers, video detection. |
| Texture loader | URL loading, cache key behavior, cancellation, retry on failure. |
| Render graph | slot validation and plan generation rules. |
| Passes | defaults and shader contract validation. |
| Error report | classification and normalized shape. |
| Recompile policy | rebuild triggers and non-triggers. |

## Key runtime guarantees validated by tests

| Guarantee | Why it matters |
| --- | --- |
| `useMotionGPU` and `useFrame` require `FragCanvas` | Prevents undefined runtime context usage. |
| `defineMaterial` freezes output | Makes material snapshots cache-safe and deterministic. |
| Pipeline signature ignores pure uniform value changes | Avoids unnecessary recompiles. |
| `useTexture` abort/reload semantics are race-safe | Prevents stale async writes. |
| `ShaderPass` contract enforcement | Keeps post-process shader interface stable. |

## Internal implementation details (important for maintainers)

### Uniform updates

- Frame uniforms (`time`, `delta`, `resolution`) are written each frame.
- Material uniform buffer uses dirty-range detection to minimize queue writes.

### Texture lifetime

- Each texture binding keeps a fallback 1x1 texture.
- Reallocation happens on format/size/source object change.
- Dynamic upload policy comes from resolved update mode.

### Pass lifecycle

- Pass instances are identity-tracked.
- `setSize` is called when resolution changes or pass first appears.
- `dispose` runs on removal or renderer destroy.

### Render target lifecycle

- Resolved definitions are signature-compared per frame.
- Only changed/removed targets are reallocated/destroyed.

### Diagnostics and profiling

- Scheduler stores last run timings and optional rolling window stats.
- `setDiagnosticsEnabled(false)` clears timing state.

## Build and validation commands

From `packages/motion-gpu`:

```bash
bun run build
bun run test
bun run check
bun run lint
```

From `apps/web`:

```bash
bun run check
bun run test
bun run lint
```

## Practical caveats

| Caveat | Guidance |
| --- | --- |
| WebGPU availability varies by browser/platform | Always expect initialization failures in unsupported contexts. |
| `autoRender = false` overrides all render modes | Use it carefully, especially during debugging. |
| `onInvalidate` texture mode is context-sensitive | Pair with explicit invalidation policy for predictability. |
| Handcrafted material objects are unsupported | Always use `defineMaterial(...)`. |

## Suggested future hardening areas

1. Add integration tests around dynamic pass list churn under load.
2. Add stress tests for frequent render target topology changes.
3. Add browser-matrix smoke tests for WebGPU feature differences.
